d%20Jake's%20death.%20My%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmisconceptions-about-human-brain-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Elogical%20brain%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20knew%20they%20were%20different%2C%20but%20my%20heart%20didn't.%20Eventually%2C%20all%20these%20feelings%20rose%20to%20the%20surface%20and%20burst%20open%20my%20Pandora's%20box%2C%20leaving%20shards%20everywhere.%20I%20found%20slivers%20everywhere%20for%20months%20after.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIronically%2C%20I'd%20always%20prided%20myself%20on%20being%20very%20attuned%20to%20my%20grief%20about%20Jake.%20I%20often%20visited%20his%20graveside%2C%20refreshing%20his%20flowers%20and%20bringing%20him%20trinkets%20from%20our%20travels.%20I%20brought%20him%20balloons%20and%20other%20silly%20things%20on%20his%20birthdays.%20I%20even%20started%20a%20foundation%20in%20his%20memory%20to%20give%20me%20an%20outlet%20to%20talk%20about%20him.%20But%20when%20Ethan%20went%20to%20school%20and%20I%20felt%20that%20void%20both%20in%20my%20house%20and%20in%20my%20heart%2C%20I%20realized%20that%20I%20never%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20dealt%20with%20the%20loss%20of%20Jake.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20he%20first%20died%2C%20I%20cried%20until%20I%20was%20raw%20for%20weeks%2C%20but%20eventually%20those%20tears%20dried%20up%2C%20and%20life%20continued.%20I%20thought%20that%20was%20the%20process%3A%20I%20grieved%2C%20and%20then%20I%20was%20done.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20once%20Ethan%20left%2C%20the%20pain%20came%20back%2C%20and%20it%20was%20worse%20than%20I%20remembered.%20It%20took%20me%20some%20time%20to%20connect%20that%20the%20pain%20was%20related%20to%20Jake's%20death.%20Slowly%2C%20I%20became%20reacquainted%20with%20my%20grief%2C%20and%20I%20let%20myself%20spend%20the%20time%20with%20it%20that%20I%20hadn't%20before.%20I%20began%20to%20understand%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.b