rong%3EWhat%20was%20Lisa%20Cook's%20early%20life%20like%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELisa%20DeNell%20Cook%20was%20born%20in%201964%20in%20Milledgeville%2C%20Georgia.%20Her%20father%2C%20Payton%20B.%20Cook%2C%20was%20a%20chaplain%20at%20Central%20State%20Hospital.%20Mary%20Murray%20Cook%2C%20her%20mother%2C%20was%20a%20nurse%20and%20the%20first%20African-American%20tenured%20faculty%20member%20at%20Georgia%20College%20and%20State%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20and%20her%20sisters%20were%20among%20the%20first%20Black%20students%20to%20integrate%20into%20local%20schools.%20She%20has%20said%20she%20has%20scars%20from%20when%20students%20beat%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20still%20have%20scars%20from%20that%20%E2%80%94%20scar%20where%20hair%20won't%20grow%20in%20my%20eyebrow%20and%20a%20scar%20on%20my%20leg%20from%20having%20been%20beaten%20during%20that%20period%2C%20during%20the%20period%20of%20desegregation%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20told%20NPR%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Civil%20Rights%20movement%20runs%20throughout%20Cook's%20family.%20Cook's%20cousin%2C%20Floyd%20McKissick%20Sr.%2C%20helped%20organize%20the%20March%20on%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222012%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%20acknowledges%20the%20crowd%20at%20the%20Lincoln%20Memorial%20for%20his%20%26quot%3BI%20Have%20a%20Dream%26quot%3B%20speech%20during%20the%20March%20on%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20on%20Aug.%2028%2C%201963.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62ad99724245600018dd97b4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222920%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%20acknowledges%20the%20crowd%20at%20the%20Lincoln%20Memorial%20for%20his%20%26quot%3BI%20Have%20a%20Dream%26quot%3B%20speech%20during%20the%20March%20on%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20on%20Aug.%2028%2C%201963.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FFile%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20uncle%2C%20Samuel%20DuBois%20Cook%2C%20was%20a%20classmate%20of%20Martin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%20at%20Morehouse%20College.%20In%201966%2C%20DuBois%20Cook%20became%20the%20first%20Black%20professor%20to%20hold%20a%20regular%20appointment%20at%20a%20white%20Southern%20university%20when%20he%20accepted%20a%20position%20at%20Duke%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmartin-luther-king-jr-facts-2019-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMartin%20Luther%20King%20Jr.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Research%20and%20Education%20Institute%20at%20Stanford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20instilled%20in%20me%20the%20deep%20belief%20of%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Movement%20that%20with%20faith%2C%20preparation%2C%20and%20great%20effort%2C%20things%20could%20and%20would%20be%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Cook%20said%2C%20praising%20her%20uncle%20and%20a%20host%20of%20relatives%20in%20April%202024%20when%20she%20accepted%20a%20lifetime%20achievement%20award%20from%20the%20Duke%20University%20center%20that%20bears%20her%20uncle's%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2263411c9a-e8cb-4394-962e-75e37747c0da%5C%22%3EWhere%20did%20she%20go%20to%20college%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201986%2C%20Cook%20graduated%20with%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20in%20philosophy%20and%20physics%20from%20Spelman%20College%2C%20a%20historically%20Black%2C%20all-women's%20university.%20While%20at%20Spelman%2C%20Cook%20became%20the%20first%20Spelman%20student%20to%20win%20the%20prestigious%20Marshall%20Scholarship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20Cook%20added%20a%20BA%20in%20philosophy%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20economics%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Oxford.%20Cook%20also%20studied%20at%20the%20Universit%C3%A9%20Cheikh%20Anta%20Diop%20in%20Dakar%2C%20Senegal.%20In%202020%2C%20she%20told%20Finance%20%26amp%3B%20Development%2C%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund's%20magazine%2C%20that%20a%20chance%20encounter%20while%20studying%20in%20Senegal%20pushed%20her%20into%20the%20field%20of%20economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20later%20earned%20her%20Ph.D.%20in%20economics%20from%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Berkeley.%20Her%20dissertation%20was%20on%20%26quot%3BExternal%20and%20Internal%20Credit%20Markets%20in%20Tsarist%20and%20Post-Soviet%20Russia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2235a1b768-fbc2-4e85-9c0b-db11c8a959c5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20appointed%20Cook%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lisa%20Cook%20is%20sworn%20in%20to%20join%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c4809957d362d375e81c24%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222971%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFed%20Chair%20Jerome%20Powell%20swore%20Cook%20into%20office%20in%202022.%3Cp%3EOlivier%20Douliery%2FAFP%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20nominated%20Cook%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Democrats%20narrowly%20controlled%20the%20US%20Senate.%20While%20Federal%20Reserve%20nominees%20are%20often%20confirmed%20with%20broad%2C%20bipartisan%20support%2C%20Cook's%20nomination%20faced%20significant%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESen.%20Pat%20Toomey%2C%20a%20Republican%20from%20Pennsylvania%20who%20at%20the%20time%20was%20the%20top%20Republican%20on%20the%20Senate%20Banking%20Committee%2C%20said%20she%20was%20%26quot%3Bgrossly%20unqualified%26quot%3B%20to%20serve%20on%20the%20central%20bank%20due%20to%20her%20lack%20of%20monetary%20policy%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BProfessor%20Cook's%20record%20indicates%20that%20she%20is%20likely%20to%20inject%20further%20political%20bias%20into%20the%20Fed's%20work%20%E2%80%94%20at%20a%20time%20when%20we%20need%20the%20Fed%20focused%20on%20fighting%20inflation%2C%26quot%3B%20Toomey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen-Sen.%20Sherrod%20Brown%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Ohio%2C%20who%20led%20the%20Senate%20Banking%20Committee