een%20warning%20about%20a%20baby%20bust%20for%20years.%20Western%20governments%20are%20taking%20action.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224220%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20in%20the%20Oval%20Office%20of%20the%20White%20House%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20on%20May%2030%2C%202025%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b6f614194a2d49b8af8c7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222813%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20has%20long%20argued%20that%20falling%20birth%20rates%20are%20the%20greatest%20threat%20to%20civilization.%3Cp%3EALLISON%20ROBBERT%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EElon%20Musk%20has%20warned%20for%20years%20that%20collapsing%20birth%20rates%20could%20threaten%20economies%20and%20society.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEurope%20and%20the%20US%20have%20stepped%20up%20this%20year%20with%20tax%20breaks%2C%20childcare%2C%20and%20expanded%20parental%20leave.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20caution%20these%20measures%20may%20not%20reverse%20fertility%20declines%2C%20citing%20Scandinavia%20and%20Hungary.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Elon%20Musk%20has%20consistently%20argued%20that%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20threats%20to%20civilization%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpronatalism-elon-musk-population-tech-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecollapsing%20birth%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20billionaire%20CEO%20believes%20that%20declining%20fertility%20could%20hollow%20out%20economies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-population-decline-worker-shortage-labor-birth-rates-immigration-economy-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eweaken%20workforces%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20leave%20the%20West%20unable%20to%20sustain%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20X%20post%20last%20week%2C%20he%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BLow%20birth%20rate%20is%20the%20number%20one%20threat%20to%20the%20West.%20There%20will%20be%20no%20West%20if%20this%20continues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20Musk%20amplified%20a%20warning%20from%20political%20commentator%20Tim%20Pool%2C%20who%20wrote%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20population%20isn't%20'collapsing'%20%E2%80%94%20it%20has%20collapsed.%20The%20shoreline%20is%20receding%20and%20no%20one%20understands%20the%20tsunami%20about%20to%20hit%20us.%26quot%3B%20Musk%20reposted%20it%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20warning%20about%20this%20since%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20century.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20governments%20in%20Europe%20and%20the%20US%20are%20taking%20steps%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-making-incentives-wont-work-experts-cash-car-subsidies-medals-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecombat%20falling%20birth%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20introducing%20policies%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20have%20more%20children%20%E2%80%94%20from%20tax%20breaks%20and%20family%20allowances%20to%20longer%20parental%20leave%20and%20subsidized%20childcare.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Musk%20has%20been%20a%20vocal%20advocate%20for%20increasing%20birth%20rates%2C%20demographers%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20he%20is%20not%20directly%20responsible%20for%20governments%20taking%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22853e8107-6afa-483b-b7bc-811b4541cc35%5C%22%3EA%20wave%20of%20pro-natal%20policies%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20France%2C%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20has%20called%20for%20a%20%26quot%3Bdemographic%20rearmament.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20his%20government%20pledged%20to%20replace%20the%20current%20low-paid%20parental%20leave%20with%20a%20new%2C%20better-paid%20%26quot%3Bbirth%20leave.%20%26quot%3B%20This%20would%20offer%20parents%20several%20months%20of%20leave%20at%20around%20half%20their%20salary%2C%20capped%20at%20%E2%82%AC1%2C900%2C%20or%20around%20%242%2C200%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20month%2C%20Spain%20passed%20a%20new%20family%20law%20extending%20paid%20maternity%20and%20paternity%20leave%20to%2017%20weeks%2C%20while%20some%20regions%2C%20including%20the%20capital%20Madrid%2C%20expanded%20their%20%26quot%3Bbaby%20check%26quot%3B%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EItaly%20is%20leaning%20on%20financial%20incentives%3A%20since%20January%2C%20mothers%20of%20two%20or%20more%20children%20have%20qualified%20for%20lifetime%20payroll%20tax%20breaks%2C%20and%20families%20can%20access%20zero-interest%20%26quot%3BFirst%20Home%26quot%3B%20loans%2C%20alongside%20child%20allowances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHungary%20extended%20its%20own%20policy%20in%20January%2C%20granting%20lifetime%20personal-income-tax%20exemptions%20to%20mothers%20of%20two%20or%20more%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20UK%2C%20typically%20cautious%20about%20family%20subsidies%2C%20launched%20one%20of%20its%20most%20ambitious%20early-years%20reforms%20in%20decades%3A%20starting%20in%20September%2C%20parents%20of%20children%20as%20young%20as%20nine%20months%20will%20be%20eligible%20for%2030%20hours%20of%20free%20childcare%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20passed%20a%20federal%20package%20in%20July%20expanding%20family%20tax%20credits%20and%20creating%20new%20savings%20accounts%20under%20the%20banner%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BWorking%20Families%20Tax%20Cut.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22FILE%20-%20This%20Feb.%2016%2C%202017%20file%20photo%20shows%20newborn%20babies%20in%20the%20nursery%20of%20a%20postpartum%20recovery%20center%20in%20upstate%20New%20York.%20According%20to%20a%20government%20report%20released%20Wednesday%2C%20May%2015%2C%202019%2C%20U.S.%20birth%20rates%20reached%20record%20lows%20for%20women%20in%20their%20teens%20and%2020s%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20fewest%20babies%20in%2032%20years.%20(AP%20Photo%2FSeth%20Wenig%2C%20File)%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5cdb93a9e9f08a3bab1ab798%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFILE%20-%20This%20Feb.%2016%2C%202017%20file%20photo%20shows%20newborn%20babies%20in%20the%20nursery%20of%20a%20postpartum%20recovery%20center%20in%20upstate%20New%20York.%20According%20to%20a%20government%20report%20released%20Wednesday%2C%20May%2015%2C%202019%2C%20U.S.%20birth%20rates%20reached%20record%20lows%20for%20women%20in%20their%20teens%20and%2020s%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20fewest%20babies%20in%2032%20years.%20(AP%20Photo%2FSeth%20Wenig%2C%20File)%3Cp%3EAssociated%20Press%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0ca5c88-788f-4aea-b47c-2598b421d2b0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Musk%20and%20some%20other%20commentators%20have%20only%20made%20the%20issue%20more%20visible'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20governments%20step%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpronatalism-elon-musk-simone-malcolm-collins-underpopulation-breeding-tech-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epro-natalist%20measures%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20demographic%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider%20it%20would%20be%20a%20mistake%20to%20see%20Musk%20and%20other%20tech%20leaders%20as%20the%20drivers%20of%20these%20policy%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConcern%20with%20low%20birth%20rates%20is%20nothing%20new%20and%20certainly%20nothing%20that%20anyone%20in%20the%20tech%20world%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20Musk%2C%20should%20get%20any%20credit%20for%20originating%20or%20leading%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ronald%20Lee%2C%20founding%20director%20of%20the%20Center%20for%20the%20Economics%20and%20Demography%20of%20Aging%20at%20UC%20Berkeley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20pronatalist%20policies%20were%20already%20widespread%20in%20Europe%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fasia-governments-have-their-birth-rate-boosting-tactics-all-wrong-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EEast%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%20decades%20ago%2C%20while%20the%20US%20Social%20Security%20system%20was%20overhauled%20in%20the%20early%201980s%20with%20aging%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETomas%20Sobotka%2C%20deputy%20director%20at%20the%20Vienna%20Institute%20of%20Demography%2C%20made%20a%20similar%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20a%20new%20topic%20among%20researchers%20and%20many%20policymakers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20citing%20France's%20family%20benefits%20dating%20back%20to%20the%201930s%20and%20Japan's%20interventions%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMusk%20and%20some%20other%20commentators%20have%20only%20made%20the%20issue%20more%20visible%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20regretfully%2C%20also%20more%20politically%20polarized.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWolfgang%20Lutz%2C%20founding%20director%20of%20the%20Wittgenstein%20Centre%20for%20Demography%20and%20Global%20Human%20Capital%2C%20was%20even%20more%20blunt%3A%20%26quot%3BTech%20leaders%20like%20Elon%20Musk%20may%20be%20experts%20in%20their%20fields%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20experts%20in%20demography.%20Their%20views%20on%20fertility%20are%20based%20on%20gut%20feelings%20and%20vague%20conjectures%20rather%20than%20scientific%20reasoning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f566df80-92a4-49ed-aa23-b208b667ddad%5C%22%3EThe%20chorus%20grows%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20tech%20leaders%20have%20echoed%20Musk's%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelegram%20CEO%20Pavel%20Durov%20has%20gone%20as%20far%20as%20to%20fund%20free%20IVF%20treatments%20at%20a%20Moscow%20clinic%20for%20women%20using%20his%20sperm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20July%202024%20Telegram%20post%2C%20he%20called%20declining%20fertility%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftelegram-ceo-funds-ivf-women-with-free-access-his-sperm-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ean%20increasingly%20serious%20issue%20worldwide%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20urged%20his%20followers%20to%20%26quot%3BDefy%20convention%20%E2%80%94%20redefine%20the%20norm!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESam%20Altman%2C%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20has%20invested%20in%20reproductive-tech%20startups%2C%20including%20Conception%2C%20which%20is%20developing%20ways%20to%20extend%20fertility%20and%20even%20enable%20two%20men%20to%20have%20biological%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b329ada17a8c5b4053cde4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Harnik%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb5d43bc-4918-4eaa-8e9b-7cdbe729c69b%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20uncertain%20fix%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-making-incentives-wont-work-experts-cash-car-subsidies-medals-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eflurry%20of%20new%20incentives%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20actually%20reverse%20the%20trend%20is%20far%20from%20clear.%20Fertility%20rates%20across%20the%20developed%20world%20have%20been%20below%20replacement%20level%20for%20decades%2C%20driven%20by%20high%20costs%2C%20delayed%20parenthood%2C%20and%20cultural%20shifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20note%20that%20lavish%20programs%20in%20South%20Korea%2C%20Japan%2C%20and%20Hungary%20have%20failed%20to%20reverse%20declining%20birth%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20said%20even%20Scandinavia's%20generous%20parental%20leave%20and%20childcare%20systems%20have%20not%20prevented%20fertility%20from%20falling.%20%26quot%3BFinancial%20incentives%20are%20mostly%20absurdly%20small%20relative%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20Hungary%20spends%20about%205%25%20of%20GDP%20annually%20on%20pro-birth%20measures%20with%20little%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESobotka%20said%20governments%20can't%20fully%20offset%20the%20costs%20and%20personal%20trade-offs%20of%20childbearing%2C%20though%20well-designed%20policies%20can%20still%20help%20parents%20realize%20their%20desired%20family%20size%20and%20lift%20fertility%20modestly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAltogether%2C%20these%20packages%20of%20family%20policies%20can%20boost%20fertility%20rates%20in%20the%20order%20of%20up%20to%200.2%2C%20maximum%200.3%20children%20per%20woman%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELutz%20was%20skeptical.%20He%20argued%20that%20while%20family%20support%20programs%20are%20valuable%20for%20child%20well-being%2C%20their%20impact%20on%20fertility%20is%20marginal%20at%20best%20and%20could%20even%20backfire%20if%20they%20push%20women%20out%20of%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnna%20Rotkirch%2C%20research%20director%20at%20the%20Population%20Research%20Institute%20in%20Helsinki%2C%20pointed%20to%20Estonia%20as%20an%20example%20where%20expanded%20family%20policies%20in%20the%202000s%20initially%20boosted%20second%20and%20third%20births%20but%20ultimately%20could%20not%20stem%20a%20collapse%20in%20first%20births%20over%20the%20past%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20new%20and%20bolder%20solutions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20also%20have%20to%20come%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplaces-support-young-motherhood-declining-birth-rate-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20city%20planners%2C%20and%20society%20at%20large%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20politicians.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20Karen%20Benjamin%20Guzzo%2C%20director%20of%20the%20Carolina%20Population%20Center%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20modest%20measures%20being%20discussed%20will%20likely%20not%20%26quot%3Bbudge%26quot%3B%20birth%20rates%20because%20they%20don't%20tackle%20the%20main%20barriers%20American%20parents%20say%20they%20face%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-baby-boom-housing-boom-home-price-affordability-parenting-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexpensive%20ho