launched%20a%20series%20of%20major%20health%20and%20infrastructure%20projects%20in%20Darrang%20worth%20over%20Rs%206%2C300%20crore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdifferent-kind-of-spiritual-joy-pm-narendra-modi-launches-rs-6-300-crore-projects-in-assam-9274919%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20quit%20my%20comfortable%20financial%20research%20job%20to%20start%20a%20drone%20company.%20Here's%20why%20I%20took%20the%20leap.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jacob%20Stonecipher%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c49f55f9db348adc0b6e2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221081%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJacob%20Stonecipher%3Cp%3ESustainable%20Skylines%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJacob%20Stonecipher%2C%2030%2C%20left%20a%20high-paying%20business-development%20career%20to%20become%20an%20entrepreneur.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20founded%20Sustainable%20Skylines%2C%20which%20uses%20drones%20instead%20of%20planes%20to%20fly%20banner%20advertisements.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBuilding%20the%20startup%20has%20been%20a%20lot%20tougher%20than%20he%20anticipated%2C%20but%20highly%20rewarding%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%2030-year-old%20Jacob%20Stonecipher%2C%20founder%20of%20Sustainable%20Skylines%2C%20a%20startup%20drone%20manufacturer%20based%20in%20Miami.%20His%20identity%20has%20been%20verified.%20This%20story%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202016%2C%20I%20was%2021%2C%20living%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20and%20working%20as%20an%20intern%20for%20a%20private-capital%20research%20firm.%20One%20weekend%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20Jersey%20shore%20with%20a%20group%20of%20friends.%20I'm%20from%20Seattle%2C%20so%20I'm%20not%20used%20to%20seeing%20airplanes%20flying%20banners%20every%20couple%20of%20minutes.%20They%20looked%20like%20they%20were%20from%20the%201940s.%20They%20were%20noisy%20and%20emitting%20a%20lot%20of%20smoke.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20couldn't%20help%20but%20think%20that%20there's%20got%20to%20be%20a%20better%20way%20of%20doing%20this%2C%20so%20when%20I%20got%20back%20to%20the%20city%2C%20I%20went%20online%20to%20learn%20as%20much%20as%20I%20could%20about%20aerial%20advertising.%20I%20became%20obsessed.%20I%20couldn't%20stop%20thinking%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20after%20I%20graduated%20from%20college%20and%20got%20a%20job%20at%20the%20same%20private-equity%20research%20company%20in%20Manhattan.%20I%20quickly%20rose%20through%20the%20ranks%20in%20business%20development%20and%20was%20making%20a%20handsome%20living.%20But%20at%20night%2C%20I%20would%20try%20to%20find%20out%20if%20a%20drone%20could%20pull%20the%20same-size%20banners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20just%20a%20lot%20of%20cold-calling%20drone%20manufacturers%20and%20shipping%20sample%2C%20800-foot%20banners%20to%20those%20willing%20to%20give%20it%20a%20try.%20Every%20single%20one%20shipped%20the%20banners%20back%2C%20saying%20this%20would%20require%20an%20entirely%20different%20software%20and%20hardware%20solution%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f542a08-4d0c-40b4-b402-76ce9091a558%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20the%20FAA's%20blessing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20would%20have%20to%20have%20the%20kind%20of%20drone%20I%20envisioned%20built%20from%20scratch.%20I%20then%20emailed%20the%20FAA%20to%20understand%20the%20process%20for%20getting%20approval%20for%20this%20novel%20operation.%20Though%20a%20few%20months%20went%20by%20without%20a%20response%2C%20I%20went%20ahead%20and%20hired%20three%20engineers%20in%20Maryland%20to%20develop%20a%20prototype%20anyway.%20I%20found%20them%20by%20searching%20LinkedIn%20and%20doing%20more%20cold-calling.%20With%20money%20from%20my%20savings%2C%20my%20mom%2C%20and%20my%20best%20friend%20from%20college%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20invest%20about%20%24150%2C000%20in%20the%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20someone%20from%20the%20FAA%20finally%20got%20back%20to%20me%20and%20said%20we%20should%20have%20a%20call.%20They%20said%20aerial%20advertising%20has%20caused%20tons%20of%20accidents%20and%20that%20it%20sounded%20like%20my%20drone%20idea%20could%20make%20the%20industry%20safer.%20By%20then%2C%20I%20had%20a%20prototype%20that%20could%20lift%20a%20heavy%20banner%20%E2%80%94%20not%20for%20a%20long%20flight%2C%20but%20long%20enough%20to%20prove%20my%20concept%20was%20feasible.%20I%20provided%20a%20demonstration%20over%20Zoom%20to%20about%20a%20dozen%20people%20from%20the%20UAS%20Integration%20Office%20of%20the%20FAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20then%20basically%20gave%20me%20their%20blessing%20to%20proceed%2C%20which%20was%20a%20big%20vote%20of%20confidence.%20It%20meant%20there%20would%20be%20a%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tunnel%20if%20we%20continued%20to%20pursue%20this.%20It%20was%202021.%20I%20named%20the%20business%20Sustainable%20Skylines%20and%20incorporated%20it.%20I%20then%20raised%20%241%20million%20from%20angel%20investors%2C%20family%2C%20and%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270ff5376-79f9-40ae-9d39-4af946bbda02%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20leap%20of%20faith%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20senior%20director%20but%20I%20quit%20my%20job%20because%20all%20I%20could%20think%20about%20was%20building%20drones%20to%20replace%20those%20old%20airplanes.%20It%20was%20almost%20unfair%20to%20my%20employer%20to%20continue%20working.%20It%20was%20certainly%20nerve-racking%2C%20a%20leap%20of%20faith%2C%20but%20I%20had%20so%20much%20conviction%20that%20I%20was%20doing%20the%20right%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20Miami%2C%20which%20is%20the%20hub%20of%20banner%20towing.%20You%20can%20test%20all%20year%20round.%20It's%20just%20a%20big%2C%20open%20space.%20We%20donated%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20ad%20inventory%20right%20out%20of%20the%20gate%2C%20just%20because%20we%20were%20learning%20how%20to%20do%20this.%20By%20the%20following%20year%2C%20the%20business%20was%20me%2C%20the%20three%20engineers%2C%20and%20my%20mom%20as%20CFO.%20She's%20been%20a%20career%20CFO.%20It's%20pretty%20special%20to%20work%20with%20your%20mom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20ago%2C%20on%20Thanksgiving%2C%20we%20got%20our%20first%20FAA%20approval%20in%20the%20US%20for%20a%20drone-based%20commercial%20operation.%20We%20launched%20our%20drone%20with%20a%20banner%20across%2010%20miles%20of%20Miami%20Beach%2C%20and%20this%20past%20spring%20break%2C%20we%20did%20our%20first%20paid%20ad%20campaign%20with%20a%20sunglasses%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d2145dec-d07f-48a7-b902-99f7d626c584%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EScaling%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20since%20opened%20a%20production%20facility%20to%20begin%20scaling%20the%20aircraft.%20Aerial%20advertising%20is%20a%20business%20we%20want%20to%20reinvent%2C%20but%20we%20also%20want%20to%20apply%20our%20drone%20technology%20to%20other%20use%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20today%2C%20we've%20raised%20%242.8%20million%20in%20seed%20funding%20and%20plan%20to%20start%20raising%20institutional%20funding%20soon.%20My%20best%20friend%20from%20college%2C%20who%20served%20seven%20years%20in%20US%20Army%20Special%20Operations%2C%20joined%20the%20team%20as%20head%20of%20government%20solutions%2C%20and%20we%20hired%20a%20chief%20marketing%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20building%20this%20business%20has%20been%20way%20harder%20than%20I%20anticipated%2C%20but%20it's%20been%20the%20greatest%20ride%20of%20my%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-researcher-quit-job-build-drone-start