ecretly%20working%20multiple%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20while%20tasked%20with%20catching%20others%20doing%20the%20same%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-secretly-working-multiple-remote-jobs-early-retirement-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3EMeet%20the%20Americans%20secretly%20working%20multiple%20remote%20jobs%20to%20afford%20early%20retirement%20%E2%80%94%20and%20making%20up%20to%20%24300K%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgot-caught-working-two-remote-jobs-fired-unethical-overemployment-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3EI%20caught%20my%20employee%20secretly%20working%20a%20second%20remote%20job.%20Here's%20why%20I%20decided%20to%20fire%20them.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22638dc579-464e-48fb-af45-743879b42c27%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EScaling%20back%20meant%20saving%20less%2C%20not%20spending%20less%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20losing%20his%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Econtract%20software%20engineering%20role%2C%20John%20updated%20his%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20and%20began%20casually%20looking%20for%20work%2C%20but%20found%20the%20job%20market%20challenging.%20He%20eventually%20asked%20a%20friend%20if%20their%20company%20was%20hiring%20%E2%80%94%20a%20conversation%20that%20led%20to%20him%20landing%20a%20part-time%20remote%20software%20engineering%20role%20that%20pays%20about%20%2450%20an%20hour%2C%20a%20gig%20he's%20held%20for%20over%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20works%20from%20home%2C%20John%20juggles%20both%20jobs%20during%20his%20roughly%20eight-hour%20workday.%20He%20expects%20to%20earn%20around%20%2460%2C000%20from%20the%20part-time%20gig%20this%20year%2C%20bringing%20his%20combined%20income%20to%20about%20%24225%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20down%20from%20%24300%2C000%20when%20he%20was%20working%20two%20full-time%20jobs.%20In%20the%20first%20few%20months%20of%20his%20part-time%20role%2C%20he%20said%20he%20billed%20about%2020%20hours%20a%20week%20and%20worked%20about%2040%20hours%20between%20his%20two%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20to%20as%20much%20as%2050%20hours%20when%20he%20held%20two%20full-time%20roles.%20John%20said%20his%20main%20employer%20knows%20he%20has%20a%20side%20gig%20of%20some%20sort%2C%20but%20doesn't%20know%20the%20specifics%20of%20the%20role%20%E2%80%94%20or%20how%20many%20hours%20he%20devotes%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20part-time%20hours%20for%20his%20second%20job%2C%20John%20said%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ejuggling%20both%20roles%20was%20manageable.%20But%20a%20few%20months%20ago%2C%20he%20chose%20to%20reduce%20his%20part-time%20work%20even%20more%20%E2%80%94%20to%20between%20five%20and%2010%20hours%20a%20week.%20With%20a%20child%20on%20the%20way%2C%20he%20said%20he%20wanted%20to%20make%20sure%20he%20had%20enough%20time%20to%20help%20with%20childcare%20responsibilities%20and%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20burnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20in%20terms%20of%20cognitive%20load%20and%20mental%20stress%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20keep%20that%20slack%20open%20for%20taking%20care%20of%20household%20duties%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScaling%20back%20his%20hours%20has%20meant%20adjusting%20to%20an%20even%20lower%20income.%20John%20still%20expects%20to%20earn%20about%20%2460%2C000%20from%20his%20part-time%20gig%20this%20year%2C%20but%20if%20he%20continues%20at%20his%20current%20pace%20%E2%80%94%20at%20just%20five%20to%2010%20hours%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20his%20annual%20earnings%20from%20his%20side%20gig%20would%20drop%20to%20around%20%2420%2C000%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20he%20began%20job-juggling%20in%202021%2C%20John%20said%20he's%20generally%20lived%20off%20his%20W-2%20income%20and%20put%20most%20of%20his%20contract%20earnings%20into%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20estimating%20that%20he's%20saved%20over%20%24150%2C000.%20He's%20managed%20to%20stick%20with%20that%20approach%2C%20so%20while%20his%20savings%20have%20grown%20more%20slowly%20with%20fewer%20contract%20hours%2C%20he's%20still%20been%20able%20to%20set%20money%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLosing%20that%20income%20has%20caused%20us%20to%20adjust%20our%20standard%20of%20living%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20but%20it's%20really%20just%20saving%20less%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20really%20spending%20less.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9049ebc-2cf8-4770-ba1c-e6fd840f992c%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe's%20trading%20a%20backup%20job%20for%20a%20backup%20plan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20said%20he%20hasn't%20had%20to%20cut%20back%20much%20on%20spending%20in%20part%20because%20he%20was%20already%20pretty%20frugal.%20During%20his%20overemployed%20years%2C%20he%20didn't%20buy%20a%20new%20car%2C%20flew%20economy%2C%20and%20often%20stayed%20at%202-to-3-star%20hotels%20when%20he%20traveled.%20Splurging%20on%20his%20honeymoon%20was%20the%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20savings%20John%20has%20accumulated%20in%20recent%20years%20have%20helped%20him%20feel%20more%20financially%20secure.%20He%20said%20he%20has%20a%20rainy-day%20fund%20that%20could%20cover%20about%20six%20months%20of%20living%20expenses%20if%20he%20lost%20his%20job%2C%20along%20with%20other%20savings%20he%20could%20tap%20in%20a%20worst-case%20scenario.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20John%20doesn't%20expect%20it%20to%20come%20to%20that%2C%20in%20part%20because%20he%20feels%20fairly%20confident%20in%20his%20job%20security%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20his%20company%20doesn't%20have%20much%20of%20a%20history%20of%20layoffs.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAnd%20if%20a%20layoff%20did%20happen%2C%20he%20feels%20pretty%20good%20about%20his%20job%20prospects.%20He%20said%20he's%20built%20a%20strong%20network%20over%20the%20years%20and%20knows%20several%20startup%20founders%20and%20hiring%20managers%20in%20his%20industry%20who%20he%20believes%20would%20help%20him%20find%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20pretty%20confident%20that%20I'd%20be%20able%20to%20secure%20another%20full-time%20job%20in%20pretty%20short%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b4fcbfb-b246-4f59-9c88-b05ab35bfb9f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EReturning%20to%20the%20office%20has%20made%20job%20juggling%20harder%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20John%20isn't%20actively%20looking%20for%20a%20second%20full-time%20job%20to%20replace%20his%20part-time%20role%2C%20he%20said%20he%20sometimes%20speaks%20to%20recruiters%20when%20they%20reach%20out%20to%20him%20on%20LinkedIn%20or%20via%20email.%20If%20a%20role%20seemed%20like%20a%20good%20fit%20%E2%80%94%20and%20flexible%20enough%20to%20lend%20itself%20to%20overemployment%20%E2%80%94%20he%20said%20he'd%20at%20least%20consider%20juggling%20two%20full-time%20roles%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20given%20that%20he's%20now%20being%20asked%20to%20work%20from%20the%20office%20a%20few%20times%20a%20month%20for%20his%20full-time%20role%2C%20John%20said%20juggling%20two%20full-time%20jobs%20would%20be%20difficult.%20One%20way%20he%20used%20to%20manage%20his%20responsibilities%20as%20an%20overemployed%20worker%20was%20by%20working%20on%20tasks%20for%20one%20job%20while%20attending%20virtual%20meetings%20for%20the%20other.%20That%20wouldn't%20be%20possible%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20really%20difficult%20to%20do%20overemployment%20on%20office%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20really%20take%20meetings%20from%20the%20office.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20John%20said%20his%20employer's%20office%20policy%20isn't%20very%20strict%2C%20and%20that%20he%20feels%20comfortable%20working%20from%20home%20all%20five%20days%20when%20personal%20commitments%20come%20up.%20Overall%2C%20he's%20grateful%20to%20still%20have%20as%20much%20flexibility%20as%20he%20does.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20nothing%20held%20against%20us%20if%20we%20can't%20make%2